## 4. Product Spotlight: Showcasing 1 of 10 Products

If a creator has 10 products configured for their livestream but only wants to showcase **one product at a time**, the system uses a **Spotlight state machine**.

```
[ Creator Dashboard ] --(Click Spotlight SKU #chair)--> [ WebSocket: activeProduct = #chair ]
                                                                       |
                             +-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
                             |                                                                                   |
                             v                                                                                   v
                [ Overlays Engine (FFmpeg) ]                                                         [ Web Embed Player ]
                             |                                                                                   |
             (Bake graphic card overlay into video)                                             (Render interactive HTML layer on web page)
                             |                                                                                   |
                             v                                                                                   v
             [ Flat Video Feed to Socials ]                                                          [ Clickable Add-to-Cart Widget ]
```

### How the Workflow Operates:
1.  **State Management:** In the database, the active stream model contains an `active_product_id` field. By default, it is `null`.
2.  **Activating a Product:** Alex clicks the **"Spotlight"** button next to Product #3 (Vibrant Gaming Chair, trigger code `#chair`) in his control panel.
3.  **The State Switch:** The control panel fires a WebSocket event `spotlight_product_change` containing the SKU details. The backend updates the database and cache, setting `active_product_id = prod_003`.
4.  **Displaying the Banner on Livestreams:**
    *   **On Social Channels (YouTube, Facebook, Instagram Live):** Since video feeds are flat, XIT must bake the banner visual directly into the video stream. The Overlays Engine uses FFmpeg's `overlay` filter. It generates an image card of the active product (including image, title, price, and trigger code) and overlays it onto the video coordinates. When Alex switches products, the engine replaces the source overlay image file, showing a transition animation on stream.
    *   **On the Web Embed Player (Website):** On Alex's storefront page, we control the media container. Instead of baking the banner into the video, the website player reads the stream metadata and renders a clean, **clickable HTML widget** on top of the player. Viewers on the website can click this widget to add the item directly to their cart.

